OL,3,CWhat are the US government long bonds
OL,4,Cand what can they forecast?
OL,6,FWhen a government issues bonds, it
OL,7,Fborrows money from investors for a
OL,8,Ffixed period, typically ranging from
OL,9,F10 to 30 years, in exchange for
OL,10,Fregular interest payments over the
OL,11,Flife of the bond.
OL,13,FThe principal amount is paid back at
OL,14,Fthe bond's maturity.
OL,16,FThe yield on a bond, or the return
OL,17,Fthat investors receive, is inversely
OL,18,Frelated to its price.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/12
