OL,3,CWhat are the US government long bonds
OL,4,Cand what can they forecast?
OL,6,FWhen demand for bonds is low, their
OL,7,Fprices drop, which causes the yields
OL,8,Fto rise.
OL,10,FConversely, when demand is high, bond
OL,11,Fprices go up and yields fall. In
OL,12,Fessence, when bond prices fall, yields
OL,13,Frise, and when prices rise, yields
OL,14,Ffall.
OL,16,FIn the case of US government long
OL,17,Fbonds, or Treasuries, the same
OL,18,Fprinciples apply.
OL,20,FWhy do long bonds matter?
