OL,3,CWhat are the US government long bonds
OL,4,Cand what can they forecast?
OL,6,FThe sell-off in the $29 trillion
OL,7,FTreasury market has caused their
OL,8,Fyields to rise, which, as a benchmark
OL,9,Ffor other interest rates, pushes
OL,10,Fborrowing costs higher worldwide.
OL,12,FMany global financial instruments,
OL,13,Fincluding corporate bonds and loans,
OL,14,Fare priced based on Treasury yields.
OL,16,FAs these yields increase, borrowing
OL,17,Fcosts for governments, businesses, and
OL,18,Fconsumers across the globe also rise.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/12
